1. The answer is C because when you experience a sudden twist, energy will impact you and inflict a force on you which pushes you into the door, which in turn exerts a force back on you
2. The answer is e because acceleration and net force are what helps the object make circular motion
3. The answer is D because when the ball exits the tube, the force of gravity will begin to push it down
4. The answer is A because, for an object to have a constant velocity, it must have no acceleration
5. The answer is E because force is reliant on distance and if the distance is the same that means the tension will be the same
